  "description": "<p>分类: <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/category/internet/\" rel=\"tag\">互联网络</a></p><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"cn.engadget.com/2013/07/05/sprint-softank-clearwire-fcc-approval/\"><img src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com/cn.engadget.com/media/2013/07/sprintwirebank.jpg\" style=\"margin: 4px;\" /></a></div>\n\n<div>所以 Bloomberg 早两天的<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/07/03/fcc-reportedly-approves-sprint-clearwire-softbank-deals/\">传闻</a>是真确的，经过美国<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2013/06/08/justice-department-clears-softbank-acquisition-of-sprint/\">司法部</a>和 Sprint 的<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2013/06/25/sprint-softbank-merger-approved/\">投资者</a>首肯之後，SoftBank 的<a href=\"http://chinese.engadget.com/2012/10/15/sprint-softbank-purchase/\">收购 Sprint 的大计</a>终於成真了，因为作为交易最後一关的美国 <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/tag/FCC/\">FCC</a> 刚刚按下图章了。在公布中，FCC 指出批准交易的（其中一项）条件就是其是否符合公众利益，而现在很明显就是 FCC 认为交易符合公众利益吧。不过不要忘记交易里还包括了 Sprint 收购 Clearwire，後者已经计划在 7 月 8 号举行股东大会，以神圣的一票去决定 Clearwire 是否接受收购；该公司的董事会已经建议接受收购。<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n经由：<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2013/07/05/sprint-softank-clearwire-fcc-approval/\">Engadget</a><br />\n引用来源：<a href=\"http://www.fcc.gov/document/fcc-approves-softbank-sprint-clearwire-transactions\">FCC</a>、<a href=\"http://newsroom.sprint.com/news-releases/federal-communications-commission-approves-softbanks-investment-in-sprint-and-sprints-acquisition-of-clearwire.htm\">Sprint</a></div><p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/07/05/sprint-softank-clearwire-fcc-approval/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">此文章网址</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/forward/20650048/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">转寄此文章</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/07/05/sprint-softank-clearwire-fcc-approval/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">回应</a><hr size=\"1\" />", 
